  "body": "NPM runs package script calls (`npm test`, `npm run yourownsscript`, `npm postinstall`, etc) with the execution environment appended with the `./node_modules` dir, so that CLI packages _don't_ need to be installed globally to work propery.\n\nCurrently there is an installation warning `npm WARN prefer global react-tools@0.13.3 should be installed with -g`, but this has not been necessary for a few NPM major versions now, so it's worth removing that warning to keep the install log clean.\n",
